<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[264,1323,284,790]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis box="[312,414,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Remarks</emphasis>
: This is the largest among the species of 
<taxonomicName box="[896,1018,684,709]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[896,1018,684,709]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Xenovarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can be easily recognised by the basal processes to the aedeagus. It shares the opening of the gonopore at midlength of shaft with H. 
<taxonomicName box="[581,705,764,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Xenovarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="compressa">
<emphasis box="[581,705,764,789]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">compressa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but only distantly related to it.
</paragraph>
